  "text": "The empirical and conceptual framework informing this study comes out of Ethnomethodology (EM). EM is interested in understanding how ordinary members of a culture mutually construct a shared sense of order and intelligibility in everyday social life [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . EM provides understanding of social action, the nature of intersubjectivity and the social constitution of knowledge. Its analytical framework permits the documentation and examination of the commonsense knowledge that ordinary members of society use to 'make sense of, find their way about in, and act on the circumstance in which they find themselves' (Heritage, 1984, p. 4 ).",
